               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en" source="#bibl000048x-2">The Sage Mother Hall, also known as the Holy Mother Hall, is the oldest building in the Jinci Shrine complex. The building has undergone repeated restoration, it first constructed in the ninth year of Taiping Xingguo (太平興國) reign period (984) (Chai 2002,11) and the current hall was likely built from 1038 to 1087 during the  <term ref="/keyword/k000055">North Song Dynasty</term>  (Miller 2007，122). From 1992 to 1995, it was overhauled due to sinking foundations and tilting of the hall (Chai 2002,15).The hall is east-west oriented and the main entrance is facing the east, which has a double-eaves hip-and-gable roof and measuring seven-bay front facade of 26.71 meters and six-bay side facades of 21.15 meters(Chai 2002,125). It is composed of a tall central section surrounded by a second set of eaves covering a veranda that is one bay deeps along the side and back facades and two bays deep along the front facade (Tracy 2007,107). Four front columns in the central and second bays are cut short and supported by three-rafter beams of front veranda that span the two-bay space.(Qi 1992, 53-57)he style of structural features suggests an eleventh-century practice in southern Shanxi province.（Miller2007，108-121）
                  Moreover, inside the hall are 43 statues from the North Song Dynasty, the carved wooden dragons on the front columns and the statue of the Sage Mother contained in the wooden shrine are the original ones to the second year of the Yuanyou(元祐) reign period.</desc>
               <desc type="builing-data" xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#bibl000048x-2">聖母殿是晉祠內現存最古的一座廟宇。建築幾經修葺，殿初建於北宋太平興國九年（柴2002,11），今建築主體的建造年代約為1038-1087（Miller2007，122）。因基礎下沈，殿身傾斜等原因，聖母殿於1992年-1995年間進行落架大修（柴2002，15）。聖母殿坐西向東。殿為重檐歇山頂，面闊七間26.71米，進深六間21.15米（柴2002，125）。四周圍廊（副階周匝），兩山及後檐廊深一間，前廊深兩間。前檐明次三間的廊下內柱改為不落地的童柱，立於前廊的三椽栿上。（祁1992,53-57）建築結構顯示是山西南部十一世紀流行的做法（Miller2007，108-121）此外，殿內有宋代雕塑43尊，神龕內的聖母像與殿堂前廊柱上的木雕盤龍是北宋元祐二年原物。</desc>                             
